oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Humphreys County Courthouse
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of the Humphreys County Courthouse located in Reynoldsburg, Tennessee.
The Humphreys County Courthouse was the county seat from 1816 to around 1837. This was torn down after the TVA bought the land for Kentucky Lake. Reynoldsburg no longer exists.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
